  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the IDPs and underserved communities in Albab District with WASH interventions by improving Water and Sewage networks and other WASH services.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project supports IDPs and host communities population in Al Bab district (Al Bab and Arima sub districts)  through WASH interventions.

To maximize the impact of the project and reduce water-borne and related diseases, WaSH intervention will be implemented as a complementary component in the project target area by extension and rehabilitation of WASH infrastructure (water network, sewage network) in addition to connecting two camps to a nearby water station and installing solar power system to operate the pumping station through rehabilitation of&quot; Shweiha  Station&quot;.  Water quality will be ensured and water will be chlorinated with FRC between 0.2 - 0.5. in addition, the WASH component will support the solid waste management system in Qabasin and its surrounding villages by providing diesel, supporting local cleaners, and waste containers, and conducting a hygiene promotion campaign focusing on COVID-19 and personal hygiene. It aims to ensure that IDPs and host communities in the targeted locations can maintain or improve their hygiene behaviors. In total, 32,497 individuals (7,799 men, 8,126 women, 8,611 boys, 7,961 girls) will benefit from the  WASH activities of this project. People with disability will be taken into consideration to ensure that they benefit from the activities, where possible garbage containers will be near them, while the pumping of water will reach all people in  the target area including PWD.</narrative>
  </description>
